2004-12-12  Vladimir Tsichevski  <wowa1@online.ru>

	* misc.scm (misc): add-printer procedure was added

2004-12-05  Vladimir Tsichevski  <wowa1@online.ru>

	* cgen.scm: a new field `argument cast' added to function argument
	specifications or object field specifications. It allows explicit
	casting to Bigloo scheme types from external types. For example,
	if C library declares argument as `const char*' and it is mapped
	to Bigloo `string', which is effectively `char*', explicit casting
	eliminates C compiler warnings about `const'.

